			<ns0:name>pa...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101628056640429344673/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently R-DFA allows all 32-bit operand instructions to produce a sandboxed operand, since they set more significant 32 bits to zero.

The production validator only allows a predefined set of instructions to sandbox an operand:
Arithmetic instructions: ADD, IMUL, LEA, NEG, SUB, XADD.
Logic instructions: AND, NOT, OR, XOR.
Assignment instructions: MOV, MOVD, MOVSX, MOVSXD, MOVZX.
Exchange instruction: XCHG.
